      "content": "I hear how heavy this feels, and it's okay to feel exhausted when you're carrying so much alone. Your children are busy with their own lives, but you are still their foundation, even if it feels like you've become just a routine. Sometimes, when the weight becomes too much, the only way to breathe is to let go of the burden and let others carry it for a while. You deserve to rest, and that is the most important thing you can do for yourself and them right now.",
